Gemini said



*Dynamic Rider Management in Networks via Rider Tags*





Managing delivery networks just got a whole lot smarter. Instead of
manually searching  and adding/removing riders one by one, you can now
fully automate adding riders in network using *Rider Tags*.


Why We Built This?










Previously, keeping track of riders in networks was a manual process. Admin
had to look up riders individually or rely heavily on static CSV uploads to
handle group assignments.


We built this feature to eliminate the administrative burden, allowing you
to manage large-scale networks effortlessly through automated, rule-based
logic.
What=E2=80=99s New!



   1.

   *Tag-Based Network Mapping:* Link a tag (and its specific values) to a
   network. The moment a rider is assigned that tag, they are instantly add=
ed
   to the network.


   2.

   *Automatic Offboarding & Cleanup:* When a tag or value is unassigned
   from a rider, they are automatically removed from any associated network=
s,
   no manual cleanup required.


   3.

   *Loaned Riders:* Tag configurations remain isolated. A borrowing
   business can apply their own tags to pull a loaned rider into their
   networks. Once the loan ends, the rider's original supplier tags and
   network attachments instantly restore.


   4.

   *Flexi Shifts:* If a rider accepts a Flexi Shift, their tag-bound
   networks are temporarily suspended. The moment the shift ends, their
   standard tag rules automatically reinstate.


What This Means To You






   1.

   *Save Hours of Admin Work:* Stop managing rosters manually. Set up your
   network tag rules once, and let the system handle the heavy lifting as y=
our
   rider list grows or changes.


   2.

   *Eliminate Human Error:* Ensure riders are never assigned to the wrong
   zones or vehicle networks. If their profile tags change, their network
   access updates instantly and flawlessly.


   3.

   *Operational Flexibility:* Effortlessly handle complex fleet scenarios,
   like peak-hour flexi shifts or borrowing/lending riders, without breakin=
g
   your permanent network structures or losing track of rider configuration=
s.

What=E2=80=99s Next

Something exciting is coming soon - Stay tuned !!
